text: Choi Jin-sil (born in December 24, 1968 – died October 2, 2008) was a South Korean actress, considered one of the best actresses in the country. She debuted in the eighties and played the leading role in 18 movies, 20 television dramas and 140 commercials. From Ad Star to Celeb-Mom She died through suicide.
